            <div class="card bg-secondary" id="1">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">1. What is FiyiStack?</h5>
                    <p>
                        FiyiStack is a <strong><u>low-code generator</u></strong> that allows you to create a table,
                        belonging to a database, and convert it into code to be manipulated by a web application. 
                        If you enter 10 columns of a table, FiyiStack <strong><u>converts them to ~5,000 lines of code</u></strong>. 
                        Thanks to this, <strong><u>you can write code faster and more securely</u></strong>. 
                        But this is not new, FiyiStack belongs to the range of programming tools as are the RAD tools. 
                        But, <a href="#2"><strong>what is a RAD tool?</strong></a>
                    </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card bg-secondary" id="2">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">2. What is a RAD tool?</h5>
                    <p>A RAD tool is a programming tool capable of <strong></><u>speeding up software development</u></strong>. It's basic qualities are:</p> 
                    <ul>
                        <li class="mt-2">Rapid development and delivery with <u>high quality</u> for a low
                            investment cost system.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">Reduce the risks of mistyping by developers, breaking the code into small fragments
                            to <u>provide easier change</u> during the development process.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">Iteration and reuse of prototypes and templates.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">Promotes the co-participation of clients with the development team.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">It includes GUI builders, database builders, fourth generation languages,
                            and object-oriented techniques.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">It emphasizes the <u>fulfillment of the requirements</u> by the users.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">Development of priorities and definitions of delivery deadlines.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">Produces the necessary documentation to facilitate future
                            development and maintenance.</li>
                    </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card bg-secondary" id="3">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">3. What generates FiyiStack?</h5>
                    <p> 
                        A web application is composed of 3 main layers. Front-end, back-end and
                        database. FiyiStack generates the 3 layers:
                    </p>
                    <p><strong>Database:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>Tables with columns</u> to store the data of your web application.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>Stored procedures</u> to communicate the tables with the back-end 
                            through functions stored in the database.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Back-end:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>C# models</u> which are C# classes. They contain the columns of each table
                            but in the form of C# properties. It also contains the functions that
                            communicate with the stored procedures of each table.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>C# services</u> which are C# classes. These classes are dedicated to the
                            user's business. Here, accesses to C# models are processed, emails are sent,
                            third-party APIs are connected and more.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>C# protocols/interfaces</u>. These interfaces are the connection between the
                            web API's of the application with the C# services.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>C# web API's</u>. These are the ones in charge of intercepting the HTTP requests
                            of the users and delegating the tasks to the C# services.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>C# filters</u>. Filters in a back-end allow you to block malicious or faulty
                            requests. If an HTTP request passes the filter, it executes the corresponding
                            web API.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Front-end:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>TypeScript models</u>. These are models which contain the names of the columns
                            stored in each table, but in property format.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>jQuery code</u>. This layer is in charge of taking the interactions by the user
                            to send or retrieve information from the API's. It also connects with
                            TypeScript models.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>Razor Pages</u>. Razor pages are responsible for giving rise to HTML, CSS and
                            JavaScript code. Every Razor page has a back-end that is only accessed if
                            the C# filters are passed.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
